This paper discusses bibliometric analysis and visualization techniques for research evaluation, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on paper and journal impact metrics suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL), which deals with the organization, retrieval, and analysis of digital information. Other relevant sub-categories include Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
